<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Zephreck</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-07 02:56:25</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>In my opinion this is a much better helm for rangers than the Crested Helm. The Crested Helm has +2 more Strength ( +6 vs +4) but has a Charisma bonus where the Executioner's hood has the more valuable (IMO) stat bonus by adding +9 Dex. Which helps with dodge, dual wield, double attacks, and weapon procs. Just my two cents but much more valuable than a Crested Helm.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Zephreck</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-07 03:03:12</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oh there is also the weight consideration. Keeping in mind that for every +1 on strength you are allowed one more point of weight the Executioner's hood has the better strength bonus. This item is EXTREMELY light. It only weights .2 that is not even a pound and gives you +4 strength.  The Crested Helm weights 5 and only gives you +6 so basically you are getting to carry one more pound by equiping this item vs the Executioner's hood. Now the damage created by the additional 2 Strength will have to be considered as well and the Additional 5 AC it provides. Personally being a Wood elf I have 119 strength now and for now am more worried about what I can carry and the weight of my items. And trust me I would much rather have the Dex bonus than the charisma bounus. </font></td></tr></table>
